DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "parserPopUp.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = non_zero_random(-5,5,1);
$h = non_zero_random(-9,9,1);
$neg_h = -$h;
$k = non_zero_random(-9,9,1);
if ($a == 1) {$f = "(x + $neg_h)^2 + $k"} 
   elsif ($a == -1) {$f ="-(x+$neg_h)^2 + $k"}
   else {$f = "$a (x + $neg_h)^2 + $k"};

if ($a >0 ){ $ans = "upward"; $word = "positive" } 
      else {$ans = "downward"; $word = "negative"};

$symm = "x = $h";


$popup = PopUp(["Choose One","upward","downward"],$ans);

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 1:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
Consider the quadratic equation \( \ f(x) = $f \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
a) What are the coordinates of the vertex?  $SPACE $SPACE ( \{ ans_rule(10) \} , \{ ans_rule(10) \} ) 
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) What is the axis of symmetry? \{ ans_rule(20) \} $BR
$BITALIC (Do not just enter a number as your answer.  Enter your answer in the form of an equation for a vertical line of symmetry). $EITALIC
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) The parabola opens \{ $popup->menu() \} .

END_TEXT

ANS( num_cmp( $h ) );
ANS( num_cmp( $k ) );
ANS( equation_cmp($symm,vars=>['x','y']) );
ANS( $popup->cmp() );


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
By comparing \( \ f(x) \) to the vertex form, \( \ y=a(x-h)^2+k \) , $SPACE we see the vertex is (${BITALIC}h $EITALIC , $BITALIC k${EITALIC})=( $h, $k). The axis of symmetry is the vertical line through the 
vertex, so the equation is \( \ x= $h \) . $SPACE  The parabola opens $ans because the value of $BITALIC a${EITALIC}=$a is $word . 
$BR
END_SOLUTION

      
ENDDOCUMENT();  